<HEADLINE> Glance of World Cup Soccer Biggest-Score Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran scored the most of 17-0 over
the Maldives in Damascus on Monday, making the 14th time in World
Cup history that one team scored at least 10 goals.
</P>
<P>
Among the best-score matches, only one was set in the finals as
Hungary whitewashed El Salvador 10-1 in Spain in 1982.
</P>
<P>
Four of them were set in qualifiers for next year's World Cup
finals in France.
</P>
<P>
The 14 best-score matches are as follows:
</P>
