<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kabila Vows to Rebuild Former Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Laurent Kabila, President of the
Democratic Republic of Cogo (DRC), today vowed to alleviate
poverty and boost economic development in his country.
</P>
<P>
Kabila, who was here attending the 33rd summit of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU), told reporters that he was
confident of meeting the challenges he was facing.
</P>
<P>
He said his country, with little external aid, would rely on
internal resources to carry out most of the development programs.
</P>
<P>
"External aid is important, but first we must count on our own
capabilities," said Kabila. "We have potentials in human
resources and wealth."
</P>
<P>
He said his country is beset by a series of difficulties like
rampant curruption, high jobless rate and poor agriculture that
were left over by the previous regime which he toppled last month
after a several-month rebelion.
</P>
<P>
Kabila said the best thing is that "we have liberated our
country," adding that even those who supported the former regime
are now backing the new government.
</P>
<P>
He said the two-year period before the proposed elections
would be used to ensure some basic infrastructure and build
support services to facilitate the transition.
</P>
<P>
"If everything goes according to plan, two years are enough
for us to prepare," he said.
</P>
<P>
Kabila, who was sworn in as President of the DRC last week,
has promised to hold elections in his country in two years.
</P>
</TEXT>
