<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC Pledges Support for AEC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The 12-member Southern African
Development Community (SADC) today pledged full support for the
African Economic Community (AEC) which held its inaugural meeting in
Harare today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting held on the second day of the 33rd summit
of the Organisation of African Unity (OAU), Mozambican President
Joachim Chissano said, ''SADC has committed itself to cooperating with
other regional economic organisations to accelerate the establishment
of the African Economic Community."
</P>
<P>
He said, ''We believe that consolidation of regional integration
process will enhance our capacity towards gradual establishment of
African Economic Community.'' he, however, felt the full impact of
African economic cooperation would be gradual.
</P>
<P>
An agreement made at a SADC Council of Ministers meeting in
February this year to sign the protocol of relations between the AEC
and the regional economic communities would provide a sound framework
for practical cooperation and dialogue, Chissano said.
</P>
<P>
''I would like to underline the importance of strengthening the
existing regional economic communities and establishing new ones
where they do not exist in order to facilitate the process of
establishment of the AEC,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He added the AEC would provide deeper cooperation and integration
of African economies which would help avoid marginalisation in the
face of growing globalisation of trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
