<HEADLINE> Ugandan President for Improvement of Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni here
today urged African countries to improve their production capacities
in the interest of national economic development.
</P>
<P>
While addressing the summit conference of the African Economic
Community at the Organization of African Unity meeting, Museveni
said that continental common market will be still-born and never see
the light of day unless African states improve their production
capacities, widen their tax bases and evolve a harmonious working
partnership with business people.
</P>
<P>
he said that it is all very well to talk about achieving African
economic integration, but this will remain a pipedream unless African
countries develop their human resources.
</P>
<P>
Museveni pointed out, "We must ensure that every African has been
to school, not only just to read and write English, or French or
Arabic as if that is education. The people must learn skills that
can feed them."  
</P>
</TEXT>
