<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Britain said today it would not
allow a visit by a delegation from the Iraqi Oil Ministry.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Foreign Office said Britain had turned
down visa applications from five Iraqi officials who planned to
hold talks on selling oil for food and medicines as part of a deal
approved by the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
