to deal with Iraq to speak to Iraqi businessman. But British
policy is to reject applications from Iraqi officials," he said.
</P>
<P>
The current oil-for-food deal calls for 2 billion U.S. dollars
worth of oil sales over six months so that Iraq can buy food and
medicine for its people, who are suffering from U.N. trade
sanctions imposed in August 1990 when Iraqi troops invaded Kuwait.
