<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Carries Out Survey on Agricultural Wage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Labour and Social
Affairs of Ethiopia has carried out a survey on agricultural wage
employment and rural non-farm employment.
</P>
<P>
The survey is presented for discussion and endorsement by a team
of experts at a seminar which is opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted with the financial and technical
assistance from the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) and
the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), is
aimed to help formulating agriculture-led industrial development
policy in the country.
</P>
<P>
Opening the seminar, Minister of Labour and Social Affairs
Hassen Abdela said poverty in rural areas has its roots mainly
in low productivity, sub-economic holdings and landlessness.
</P>
<P>
He added that small and fragmented farm-sized and low level
technology have reduced the capacity of farmers to undertake long-
term investment on the farm.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 90 percent of Ethiopia's population live in rural areas
and 85 percent of its labour force is engaged in rural activities
to earn its living. enditem

