<HEADLINE> Ethio-German Consultation Meeting Opens in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A two-day Ethio-German
consultation meeting opened here today with the objective of
reviewing the progress of on-going projects and programs financed
by Germany.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Ethiopian Vice-Minister of Economic
Development and Cooperation Mulatu Teshome said Ethiopia's
development strategy is centered on the agricultural
development-led industrialization and the simultaneous and
integrated development of agriculture and industry.
</P>
<P>
He told the German delegation that the overall development
strategy is supported by sectoral development strategies and
policies formulated to address sector-specific issues.
</P>
<P>
Head of the German delegation Brigit Frohlich said for German
development cooperation, Ethiopia has again become a target,
adding that almost all instruments and organizations of German
development cooperation have taken up their work in Ethiopia with
additional funds coming in.
</P>
<P>
She said Germany will concentrate on on-going cooperation
activities in the sectors agreed upon rather than embarking on
new ones, adding that these sectors are agriculture and resource
management, road maintenance, water supply, primary education and
vocational training.
</P>
<P>
According to the German delegation, Germany's share in the
assistance accorded to Ethiopia by the European Union (EU)
accounts for 26 percent.
</P>
<P>
The government of Germany donated about 57 million US Dollars
in development assistance to Ethiopia last year. 
</P>
