<HEADLINE> Angola to Implement Rural Trade Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Angola will carry out a long term
trade program in its rural areas to promote their development,
Minister of Agriculture Carlos Fernandes said here today.
</P>
<P>
He announced the Angolan government's decision at a news
conference held here today.
</P>
<P>
The minister of agriculture noted that to recover domestic
production is a top priority during the first phase of Angola's
national economic rehabilitation, while trade in rural areas is a
key factor for agricultural production and development.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the government has decided to implement the long
term agricultural trade program to improve trade in rural areas,
he added.
</P>
<P>
The program's main focuses include rebuilding trade networks
in rural areas and promoting development of rural markets, he
revealed, adding that the government will allocate five million
US Dollars for rebuilding and repairing the war-torn
infrastructure in the implementation of the program.
</P>
<P>
The program will be started in the near future, the minister
said. 
</P>
