<HEADLINE> US Welcomes Romania-Ukraine Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. today congratulated
Romania and Ukraine on the signing of a treaty for closer
relationship.
</P>
<P>
"We understand that this treaty confirms their present borders,
protects the rights of ethnic minorities in each country, and lays
the basis for close... cooperation between the two countries,"
State Department Spokesman Nicholas Burns announced.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of Romania and Ukraine signed the Bilateral Treaty of
Friendship and Cooperation earlier today to promote cooperation
between them.
</P>
<P>
"This treaty constitutes a very important contribution to the
building of an undivided Europe rooted in common values of
democracy and cooperation," Burns told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He added that the U.S. "believes that a more integrated Europe
is a good thing both for Europe and the United States." The
Romania-Ukraine treaty is a "very important development," he
stressed. 
