<HEADLINE> UN Chief Appoints New Representative to Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General Kofi
Annan decided today to appoint Lakhan L. Mehrotra of India as his
representative to Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Mehrotra has held various government, diplomatic and academic
posts, including his government's ambassador to Argentina,
Uruguay, Paraguay and Yugoslavia (1982-89), secretary in the
Ministry of External Relations (1990-92), special envoy of the
prime minister of India for Africa (1991-92) and high commissioner
of India in Sri Lanka (1989-90).
</P>
<P>
Mehrotra, born in 1934, was closely associated with the peace
process in Cambodia beginning with the Preparatory Meeting for the
International Paris Peace Conference and including the conference
itself. He also participated in the Ministerial Conferences on
Rehabilitation and Restoration in Cambodia held in Tokyo in 1992
and was team leader of the UNDP (United Nations Development
Program)-sponsored Public Administration and Civil Service Reform
Mission in Cambodia in 1993. 
</P>
