<HEADLINE> Saudi FM in Jordan on Peace Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabian Foreign Minister
Prince Saud al-Faisal arrived here today in an effort to salvage
the deadlocked peace process.
</P>
<P>
King Hussein of Jordan met with the Saudi foreign minister this
evening at the Royal Court and both sides discussed the peace
development in the region and issues of bilateral ties, Jordan
Television reported.
</P>
<P>
But details of the meeting were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
On his arrival in the kingdom, the Saudi foreign minister told
the press that Saudi Arabia is making an effort to activate the
peace process since no breakthrough was made by the international
efforts to bring the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks back on
track.
</P>
<P>
The hardline policy of the Israeli government has plunged the
peace march into a dead corner, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Mideast peace process has been stalled again for about
three months since Israel started building new Jewish settlement
in Har Homa in Arab East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
Saudi-Jordanian relations cooled down during the 1990-1991
Gulf crisis (1990-1991) because Jordan sided with Iraq when it
invaded Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral ties between Jordan and Saudi Arabia was warming
up after Jordan distanced itself from Iraq in a bid to end its
isolation from other Arab states and the West since the end of
the Gulf crisis. 
</P>
