<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Strike over delayed payment of
salary arrears staged by over 200 general workers of the
University Teaching Hospital (UTH), the biggest hospital in
Zambia, entered its second today, paralyzing operations.
</P>
<P>
The workers are demanding payment of their may salaries and
five months of arrears of the 30 percent increment awarded to
civil servants by the government in January this year.
</P>
<P>
The arrears had been paid to all other civil servants by the
end of last month and the UTH workers wondered why they had been
left out.
</P>
<P>
The management of the hospital today called on the striking
workers to resume work immediately,saying the strike is illegal.
</P>
<P>
A circular delivered to the striking workers this morning said
that the management is ready to protect all those who are willing
to call off their strike. The management also said in the
circular that their grievances are being looked into.
</P>
<P>
But union Chairman Lasson Mapulanga said the workers will
continue with their strike until the demands are met. 
</P>
