<HEADLINE> China Takes Elders Team Title at Rhythmic Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese gymnasts were ushered in
as champions in the elders team event of the Four Continents
Championships in Rhythmic Gymnastics here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese squad collected their winning total of 111.921
points, beating Japan to second in 111.537 and South Korea to
third in 109.274.
</P>
<P>
In the team all-around event, Japan reap its first gold in
37.75 points, beating China to second in 36.90 and Australia third
in 36.05 points.
</P>
<P>
Early this morning, the United States took the first gold medal
in the junior team event, beating Japan and Canada to second and
third respectively while China failed to field in its junior
entries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Zhou Xiaoqing currently ranked first in the individual
all-around competition with 37.586 points.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Xiaoqing, the Atlanta Olympian, who made a clean sweep of
four gold medals in the 1995 Cairo Championships, also scored the
event-high 9.500 points in the loop competition.
</P>
<P>
Egle Abruzzini, president of the technical committee of the
International Gymnastics Federation, said the Chinese girls
displayed their top forms with good compositions and on-spot
performances.
</P>
<P>
Other 12 gold medals will be competed in the coming two days,
and China is expected to bag home two more golds.
</P>
<P>
The Four-Contients Championships features a total of 150
entries in 18 squads from Asia, America, Oceania and
Africa. 
</P>
