<HEADLINE> French Communists Vote to Join New Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- French Communist Party members
nationwide voted overwhelmingly Tuesday night to join the new
Socialist government led by Lionel Jospin, party officials said
today.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time the Communists have been part of a
French government since 1981. They have been given the ministries
of youth and sports, transport and equipment, and the state
tourism secretariat.
</P>
<P>
While some 70-80 percent of party members at local level backed
the decision by the party's national council to join the
government, most members in the northwestern department of
Nord-Pas-de-Calais voted against, claiming the party's conditions
for participation "insufficient."
</P>
<P>
The party, which won 38 seats in last week's legilative
election, was invited to joint the government by the Socialist
Party which failed to get enough seats for an absolute majority in
parliament. 
</P>
