<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's State Council Adopts Draft Education, Flood Control Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The 57th meeting of the Executive
Committee China's State Council, presided over by Premier Li Peng,
was held today and adopted in principle drafts of the Higher
Education Law and Flood-Control Law, and Public Security
Department Supervision Regulations.
</P>
<P>
Those present praised the progress the country's higher
education has made since the founding of the People's Republic,
and especially since the reforms and opening up started in the
late '70s, but said that a special law on higher education is
still necessary.
</P>
<P>
They pointed to the importance of a flood-control law because
of the frequent occurrence of flooding. Rapid growth in the
economy, the population, and the size of urban areas has caused
many new problems, and a law would help legalize flood-control
efforts.
</P>
<P>
It was decided that the two draft laws will be revised and
submitted to the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress for examination.
</P>
<P>
A special task force to oversee the police force to make it
cleaner and fairer is also necessary, it was pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The regulations will be promulgated by the State Council after
revisions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
