<HEADLINE> Beijing Elects New Vice-Mayor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Yue Fuhong, a 47-year-old Beijing
native, was elected vice-mayor of Beijing at a meeting of the
Standing Committee of the Beijing Municipal People's Congress
today.
</P>
<P>
Yue is a member of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and has
served as a middle-school teacher, deputy-magistrate of Tongxian
County in suburban Beijing, magistrate of Huairou County in
suburban Beijing, and was assistant Beijing mayor in charge of
agriculture, before being elected as vice-mayor.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin said, "Yue is familiar with
agriculture and rural affairs and has done an outstanding job in
his former positions."
</P>
<P>
Yue will remain in charge of agriculture as vice-major, an
official at the city government said.
</P>
<P>
His predecessor Duan Qiang, who was unable to continue his work
because of illness, has obtained approval from the CPC Central
Committee and the Municipal government to leave his position and
attend to his illness while studying at the CPC Central Committee
Party school. 
</P>
