<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Rafter on Wednesday became
the first Australian in 20 years to reach the semifinals of the
French Open.
</P>
<P>
In a match between two unseeded players, Rafter beat Galo
Blanco of Spain 6-3, 7-6 (7-3) and 6-3 in two hours and seven
minutes.
</P>
<P>
The last Australian to play in the French Open semifinals was
Phil Dent, and the last Australian champion at Roland Garros was
Rod Laver in 1969.
</P>
<P>
So far, Australia has won the most of 11 titles from the
tournament. 
