<HEADLINE> Khamenei Says Iran Never Gives in to Enemies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei
vowed here today that Iran will never give in to enemies even
for an hour though the late spiritual leader Ruhollah Mousavi
Khomeini passed away for eight years.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a big gathering at Khomeini's Mausoleum in
southern Tehran, Khamenei said that "the Iranian people will work
hard toward perfection, prosperity, knowledge and sciences."
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Khamenei touched upon the sensitive issue of
the youth. He criticized the Shah's regime for ignoring the
fate of youth and completely ignoring people's will.
</P>
<P>
He said that the massive turn-out in the 7th presidential
election on May 23 was the result of following advise by the late
spiritual leader Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
Today is the 8th anniversary of the demise of Khomeini, the
father of the Islamic revolution and the founder of the Islamic
Republic of Iran.
</P>
<P>
Black-clad mourners have converged from various parts of Iran
as well as from several other countries to pay homage to the
memory of Khomeini, who lit the first sparks of the Islamic
revolution in June 5, 1963 and was forced into exile by the
monarchy, then returned to Iran in 1979 to establish the Islamic
republic.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the mausoleum were outgoing President Akbar
Hashemi Rafsanjani, President-elect Seyyed Mohammad Khatami,
Interior Minister Ali Mohammad Besharati and several other senior
officials as well as some ambassadors.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said that the Islamic system itself is chosen by the
people and the people consider the Islamic system as their
own. However, he warned that "backwardness and passivity are
threats to the Islamic revolution." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
