<HEADLINE> China-EU Joint Declaration on Communications Cooperation Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China and the European Union (EU)
signed a joint declaration here today on expanding cooperation in
information and communications fields.
</P>
<P>
The joint declaration is signed by Song Jian, state councillor
and minister in charge of the State Science and Technology
Commission (SSTC), and Dr. Martin Bangemann, commissioner of the
European Commission responsible for industrial affairs,
information and communication technology.
</P>
<P>
