<HEADLINE> Beijing To Improve Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of Beijing
is taking measures to improve the investment environment to make
breakthroughs in introduce overseas investment, according to Mayor
Jia Qinglin.
</P>
<P>
Municipal government departments should provide high quality
services to overseas-backed enterprises, help them resolve
difficulties cropping up in production and management, and
extortion and illicit charges are strictly prohibited, Jia
stressed.
</P>
<P>
The mayor asked all government departments to improve working
efficiency, observe rules, and improve regulations, in order to
pursue internationally-accepted practices in using overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
"We will make sure that overseas investors have good prospects
of gain," he said.
</P>
<P>
The major areas for overseas investment include urban
infrastructure, high-tech industries, the service sector, and
housing projects.
</P>
<P>
To date, Beijing has approved 12,854 joint ventures, involving
more than 20 billion US dollars of contractual investment. 
