<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Reports Record Passenger Flow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
registered a record passenger flow of 787,523 during the first
five months of the year.
</P>
<P>
The number of passengers using the airport doubled that in the
same period of last year, the Macao Airport authorities said in a
press release today.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of 1996, the airport handled only
359,293 passengers.
</P>
<P>
The press release says the passenger flow has kept growing
since the beginning of the year, with the month of May seeing
189,925, the highest monthly figure.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the cargoes handled by the airport in the first five
months also increased by more than three times over a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
The airport transported almost 15 million kilograms of goods
from January to May, as compared with more than 4 million
kilograms in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurated in November 1995, the airport has opened air routes
to more than 20 destinations around the world. A total of 19 world
air companies are using the airport.  
</P>
</TEXT>
