<HEADLINE> Australian Shares Mark Time as Blue Chips Shine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Australian shares marked time
today as a lower gold price and end of financial year
book-squaring limited the market's gains.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries index ended just 2.3 points higher at 2615.9
while in New York overnight the Dow Jones industrial average rose
22.75 points.
</P>
<P>
Select buying of key blue chips Coca-Cola Amatil, Commonwealth
Bank of Australia, BHP and Lend Lease Corp bolstered the market.
</P>
<P>
"It was a mixed day with the focus really on those few blue
chips," a Sydney-based trader said.
</P>
<P>
"It was a fairly reasonable market, but we're entering that
period where the institutions step back for a bit of end of
financial year book-squaring," he added.
</P>
<P>
Coca-Cola Amatil surged 4.55 percent or 70 cents while
Commonwealth Bank shares finished 31 cents up and BHP 10 cents.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials index ended just 2.4 points firmer at
4080.8 and the All Resources index edged up 2.5 points to close at
1491.2.
</P>
<P>
The gold index slipped 3.6 points to 1566 while gold bullion
closed in Sydney at 343.7 U.S. dollars an ounce.
</P>
<P>
Data showing a 0.9-percent increase in gross domestic product
in the March quarter had little impact on shares.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 383.65 million shares worth 1.002
billion Australian dollars (761.5 million U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
