<HEADLINE> Romanian Junior Champion Banned for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Andreea Burlacu, world
junior 400 meters champion, has been banned for two years after
testing positive for the steroid nandrolone, the Romanian
athletics federation said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The federation said that Burlacu was tested positive last year
for nandrolone, which was subject to a four-year ban under
International Amateur Athletic Federation rules, but imposed a
two-year ban to the runner.
</P>
<P>
"Under new Romanian sport rules introduced last November, the
federation can impose a two-year ban for an initial offence, with
subsequent offences subject to a life ban," explained Traian
Badea, deputy secretary of the federation. 
</P>
