<HEADLINE> China Publishes Accounting Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Finance
(MOF) has published a detailed set of accounting standards for
business enterprises, the ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
The new standards, officially known as Disclosure of Relevant
Party Relationships and Transactions, are the first detailed
accounting standards published by the ministry after the release
of a similar set of standards in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The new standards are aimed at regulating the disclosure of
information about listed companies' relationships and transactions
with related parties. This will increase the openness in
accounting information of listed companies.
</P>
<P>
A MOF news release said that the implementation of the new
standards will play a positive role in the stock market
supervisory body's effort to improve its work.
</P>
<P>
It also said that right now the new standards will be limited
to listed companies. As of January 1 this year, listed companies
were required to observe the new standards when preparing their
financial sheets.
</P>
<P>
The MOF added that it will gradually formulate and publish
other accounting rules in order to further improve the quality of
the listed companies' accounting information and aid the healthy
development of the stock market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
