<HEADLINE> ADB Launches Global Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
said today that it launched a one billion U.S. dollar global bond
issue on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bond was floated in London and offered simultaneously in
the major capital markets worldwide, the Manila-based bank said.
</P>
<P>
The issue, the ADB's third and largest-ever US dollar global
bond, was floated through a syndicate jointly managed by Goldman
Sachs International, SBC Warburg and Tokyo-Mitsubishi
International.
</P>
<P>
The bond, with a coupon rate of 6.75 percent per annum and a
10-year straight maturity, was priced at 99.427 percent. It would
be listed on the Luxembourg, Hong Kong and Singapore stock
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1966 to promote economic growth in the
Asian-Pacific region, the ADB has 56 members.  
</P>
