<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Eleven Turkish military personnel
were killed today when a helicopter crashed in northern Iraq,
Turkish military sources said here.
</P>
<P>
The sources, who declined to be named, told Xinhua that the
helicopter crashed in Zap region of northern Iraq at about 07:00
local time (04:00 GMT), killing eight officers, two
noncommissioned officers and one soldier.
</P>
