support of air bombings and artillery fire, have carried out
cross-border military operations in northern Iraq since mid-May
to attack the PKK, which has been fighting an almost 13-year-old
separatist war for autonomy in eastern and southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
More than 23,000 people, including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops, have been killed in conflicts since August
1984 when the PKK started to attack military and civilian
targets in Turkey. 
