<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Applies CAD Technology With Success (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China's use of Computer Aided
Design (CAD) technology has revolutionized industrial design and
production.
</P>
<P>
To date, CAD has been applied at more than 10,000 research
institutes and 2,000 industrial manufacturers in 23 provinces and
cities.
</P>
<P>
CAD technology is used in a wide range of fields including
machine building, electronics, automobile, ship-building,
navigation, space, light industry, textiles and engineering design.
</P>
<P>
A total of 800 million yuan have been allocated for CAD
application. Over 250,000 scientists and technicians, many of whom
are research fellows and Ph.D students, have been involved.
</P>
<P>
CAD, an important aspect of electronic information, is a shared
technology that can transform traditional industries with new and
high technology, said Shi Dinghuan, director of the Industrial
Department under the State Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
As CAD replaces traditional drafting by hand with computers, it
shortens the cycle of developing a new product by 20 to 50 percent
and save a huge amount of money and raw materials as a result of
performing computer simulations, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang Transformer Plant saved 13 million yuan for
purchasing raw materials for analogue simulation in the 1988-89
period. The cycle of developing a new product is now three to five
times shorter than before CAD was implemented.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970604.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
