<HEADLINE> China Applies CAD Technology With Success (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Designs with CAD technology conform to the required standard
with technical accuracy, the plant director said.
</P>
<P>
CAD helped the plant become more competitive at home and
abroad, he added.
</P>
<P>
China began to develop CAD in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, minister in charge of the State Science and
Technology Commission, described CAD as a golden key to the market
economy for industrial firms, permitting entry to overseas
markets, and an essential component for improving the
technological creativity of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A computer expert predicted that the coming four years will see
a fast development of CAD application in China.
</P>
<P>
The country is to build three to five CAD software development
bases with a domestic market share reaching 40 percent and some
technical consultancy centers by the year 2000, an electronic
expert said.
</P>
<P>
By then, CAD will be introduced to 90 percent of institutes
engaging in engineering design, 80 percent of electronic,
automobile and ship manufacturing firms, 70 percent of machinery
and light industrial enterprises and half of the textile mills.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning, a pilot area for CAD application, is to build three
CAD development centers, one for software development, one for
hardware research, and the other for personnel training.  
</P>
