<HEADLINE> East Africa to Set up Digital Transmission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Kenya, Tanzania and Uganda, all
the three members of the East Africa Cooperation (EAC), are
planning to start an EAC digital transmission telecommunications
project this year, the Daily Nation reported today.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to improve the telecommunications
linkage between the three member states.
</P>
<P>
In addition, plans are underway for the introduction of an
east African stock exchange, the report quoted an economist with
the EAC Secretariat, Peter Kiguta, as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the capital and securities market of the three member
states have been cooperating to facilitate the establishment of
the exchange.
</P>
<P>
The EAC will also conduct seven studies on regional tourism,
the Inter-University Council for East Africa, a common external
tariff for the region and other areas. 
</P>
