<HEADLINE> Mongolia Holds Trade Fair to Attract Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian Prime Minister
Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan today called on foreign countries to make
more investment in his country.
</P>
<P>
He made the call at a two-day trade fair co-sponsored by the
Mongolian government and the World Bank to attract foreign
investment to boost oil and gas exploitation and mining in the
country. The trade fair was opened here today.
</P>
