<HEADLINE> Non-Government Technological Development in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The city of Fuzhou, capital of
Fujian Province, now has 450 non-governmental scientific and
technological organizations, undertaking research in the fields of
electronics, environmental protection, energy, biology, agronomy,
and edible mushrooms.
</P>
<P>
The organizations have helped brought in 1.6 billion yuan in
output value and 250 million yuan (30 million US dollars) in
pre-tax profits a year. Their research projects have won 813
patents.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 28 of the organizations' discoveries were applied to
production, bringing in some 30 million yuan (3.6 million US
dollars) in economic returns.
</P>
<P>
Hi-tech products developed by the organizations have been
exported to Japan, the United States, and countries in southeast
Asia.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the city has 25 overseas-funded non-governmental
enterprises involved in scientific and technological research,
generating more than 500 million yuan (60 million US dollars) in
output value a year.
</P>
<P>
All organizations and enterprises in the sector in Fuzhou earn
20 million US dollars in foreign exchange from exports each year.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
