<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Closes Restaurants to Check Spread of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibar government on
Tuesday ordered closure of all restaurants to check the spread of
cholera which has so far killed 31 people and affected more than
200 others in the Isles, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The order follows reports submitted to the government by a
committee set up by the Ministry of Health to supervise measures
to contain the killer disease that the epidemic is on the
increase.
</P>
<P>
The report showed that an average of about seven cholera cases
are reported a day and one or two people die of the epidemic a
day.
</P>
<P>
The report further said that most of owners and operators of
restaurants in Zanzibar did not observe hygiene and posed a
threat to lives.
</P>
<P>
Cholera broke out in Zanzibar on March 28 and the report said
that the disease is on the increase especially in villages and
most of those affected were women and children.  
</P>
