<HEADLINE> Rural Children Given TV Sets, Movies, Cartoons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Children at 20 Hope primary schools
in northwest China's Qinghai Province can now watch TV or cartoon
videos at school.
</P>
<P>
Three Chinese companies donated 50 films on video, 81 cartoon
videos, and TV sets and video recorders to Hope primary schools in
Qinghai Tuesday, as gifts for the International Children's Day
which falls on June 1 each year.
</P>
<P>
Groups or people from eastern part of China, which is more
economically developed than the western part, lined up to make
donations for educational growth in poor areas of Qinghai this
year.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai now has 31 primary schools that were built with money
from the Hope Project, an educational fund started eight years ago
to allocate donations for poor children so that they can go to
school or continue schooling.
</P>
<P>
Headmasters of the Hope primary schools believed that the
audio-visual equipment will help improve teaching as well as
broaden the perspective of rural children at school.  
</P>
