<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Attack Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains attacked Hong Kong
last night and this morning with more than 100 millimeters of rain
fallen across the territory.
</P>
<P>
The rains caused road flooding, landslide, traffic suspensions
on some streets.
</P>
<P>
The most severely stricken districts were Sham Shui Po, Kwun
Tong, Mong Kok, Ngau Tau Kok and Lai Chi Kok. Motorists are urged
not to drive in the Kowloon West Region.
</P>
<P>
There were 31 landslips in the past 24 hours in Hong Kong, most
of which occurred in Kwai Chung and North Kowloon, according to
the Geotechnical Engineering Office's Emergency Control Center of
the Civil Engineering Department.
</P>
<P>
At Lai Chi Kok, landslips destroyed a house with six people
stranded in it this morning. After they were rescued, a
four-year-old boy was found dead.
</P>
<P>
The Education Department issued a special announcement that
bi-sessional schools are closed this afternoon and pupils
attending morning classes and whole-day schools should not be
released until conditions are safe.
</P>
<P>
All courts, tribunals, court registries and offices were also
closed today until Thursday.  
</P>
