<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Rescue of 3 Hostages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos today directed
the safe rescue of a local government official and two of his
companions abducted by a para-military group in the southern
Philippines last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The president issued the order to Secretary of the Department
of Interior and Local Government Robert Barbers and Intelligence
Chief of the Philippine National Police Cecilio Penilla.
</P>
<P>
In a handwritten memorandum, President Ramos asked them to give
a feedback to the Office of the President as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said Vice Mayor Romeo Dela Torre and two
of his companions were snatched by the para-military group on
their way back to the town of Sabagat, Agusan del Sur province.
</P>
<P>
Police said the kidnappers sent a letter to the police, saying
they would kill the captives at the first sight of a police or
military rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
Kidnapping has been a serious problem in the country. A total
of 241 people were kidnapped last year, with millions of pesos in
ransoms being paid by the hostages' families.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government has taken measures to curb the
rampant incidence of the crime, but achieved little progress.
</P>
</TEXT>
