<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flood Prevention Work in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Wuhan, the capital of Hubei province
and a major port on the middle reaches of the Yangtze River, is
increasing efforts to protect itself against flooding, which
experts expect to be worse this year than last.
</P>
<P>
The city has spent 20.5 million yuan on water resource projects
since winter, 30 percent more than for the same period last
year. It did a record amount of work repairing or strengthening
287 km of river banks and dikes.
</P>
<P>
Last year, flooding in the city was the worst in 100 years, but
a major disaster was avoided because soldiers and local residents
worked together to build up dams.  
</P>
</TEXT>
