<HEADLINE> 1 Killed in Road Mishap in Central Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- One person was crushed to death
while another was injured Tuesday in a road mishap in Cebu City,
the central Philippines, news reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy happened when an overloaded passenger bus
sideswiped another parked bus due to the driver's misjudgment. The
victims were clinging to the handrails of the bus door, their
bodies protruding outside the packed vehicle, the report said.
</P>
<P>
One of the victims died on the scene, the other was admitted to
a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
The accident came just a day after the Land Transportation
Office announced that it would strictly enforce a ban against
overloading of passengers in buses. 
