<HEADLINE> Consortiums Bid For Three Gorges Project's 2nd Phase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Six consortiums formed by local
construction companies bid for the second phase of the Three
Gorges Hydropower Project. Their bidding prices were made public
here in Central China's Hubei province on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The second phase, open only to domestic bidders, includes civil
buildings, metal structures and equipment installations. Total
cost of the second phase is estimated to be six billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project, started in 1993, will be
completed this year. To date, 21 billion yuan has been invested in
fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
In 2003, when the second phase is completed, the first group of
generators will become operational.
</P>
<P>
Construction firms are currently preparing for the
river-blocking scheduled in November. 
