<HEADLINE> Cruzeiro Beats Gremio in Libertadores Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Cruzeiro defeated Gremio to reach
the semi-finals of the Libertadores Cup in Porto Alegre, Brazil on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Cruzeiro, champions in 1976, went through 3-2 on aggregate
despite losing Tuesday's second leg 2-1 away to Gremio, winners in
1995 and semi-finalists last year.
</P>
<P>
However, neither team really deserved to remain in the
competition after a 61-foul match in which the finer arts of the
game were put to one side in favour of rough-arm tactics.
</P>
<P>
Ignoring the best traditions of Brazilian soccer, the teams
adopted a cynical approach and concentrated their energies on
kicking, provoking and threatening opponents.
</P>
<P>
Chile's Colo Colo, Cruzeiro's semi-final opponents next month,
will be well advised to ensure their first aid kit is well stocked
before visiting Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Cruzeiro increased their aggregate lead when Fabinho, who was
limping with a hamstring injury and about to be substituted, found
enough energy to get forward and knock in a far-post cross on the
hour.
</P>
<P>
Gremio, who had received six red cards in their previous nine
games in the competition, staged a late fightback when former
Brazil international Mauro Galvao and Ze Alcino scored twice in
three minutes.
</P>
<P>
Even coach Evaristo Macedo was banned from the touchline after
an incident in a previous round when he was also sent off.
</P>
</TEXT>
