<HEADLINE> Automobile Production, Sales Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEEW DELHI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Production and sales of
automobiles in April this year registered a fall in India compared
to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the monthly flash report on production and sales
of automobiles in April 1997, all automobile companies
manufacturing four-wheelers registered a fall in sales and
production this year except for Maruti Udyog LTD, an Indo-Japanese
joint venture.
</P>
<P>
Total automobile production of four wheelers in April 1997,
fell to 28,311 compared to 28,518 in April 1996. Total sales also
registered a fall at 27,149 in April 1997 compared to 28,205 in
April 1996.
</P>
<P>
Companies registering a fall in both production and sales
include Hindustan Motors, Mercedes Benz and Telco.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not give reasons for the fall both in
automobile production and sales this year.  
</P>
