<HEADLINE> Largest Drug Case in Southwest China's Sichuan Concluded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Seven drug traffickers were
sentenced to death by the Intermediate People's Court of Chengdu
in Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the court, the drug trafficking gang, headed by
Zhang Yukun, engaged in inter-provincial drug trafficking in
collusion with overseas drug traffickers since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Zhang purchased a total of 37.3 kg of heroin in the border
region of Yunnan Province and shipped it to Guangzhou, Kunming,
and Shenzhen for sale. He received about one million yuan and
800,000 HK dollars for the drugs.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yunhua purchased 64 kg of heroin in March and May of 1993
and shipped it to Guangzhou, Chengdu and Shenzhen, where the drug
was sold for some 2.7 million yuan. Yang Yanwei purchased 65.3 kg
of heroin in the border region of Yunnan Province and sold it to
Zhang Yukun for 1.33 million yuan. Zhang Yukun and Lu Wei then
sent the drug to Cheng Jiaqiang, a drug trafficker, in Shenzhen
and obtained some 2.1 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yukun and Lu Wei were caught by the police in Shenzhen in
January 1994. The police investigated and pursued the
case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
