revenues of 600 billion baht (24 billion US dollars), Piyanat, who
oversees the Tourism Authority of Thailand (TAT), was quoted today
by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has long been the country's leading foreign exchange
earner. Last year, about 7.2 million foreign tourists visited
Thailand earning the country more than 7 billion US dollars) in
foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
"This is a good chance to promote the country. In 1998 Thailand
will host the Asian games and a number of big ceremonies to
celebrate the sixth cycle of the King of Thailand," Piyanat said.
</P>
<P>
During the campaign, the TAT will focus its promotion effort on
40 key markets in the Asia-pacific, Europe and the United States.
East Asia will be the main target.
</P>
<P>
The TAT has targeted shopping as the best means of increasing
foreign exchange during the coming two years and has plans to
spearhead a number of promotional campaigns such as discount
coupons for tourists and a central shopping district in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
With the cooperation of local department stores, "national
sales" will be organized every June and November to attract
international spenders, and a better system of tax refunds will be
implemented to support that project.
</P>
<P>
Thai food will also be on show, with the organization promoting
Amazing Thailand at 4,000 Thai restaurants around the world. There
will also be a Thai food conference in Thailand in July to
publicize Thai cuisine.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
