<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chittagong Port Users Threaten Work Abstention Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The users of Bangladesh's largest
Chittagong port has given ultimatum to the government to concede
to its demand for use of private equipment in the cargo handling
by June 5, port sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The Port Users Forum of Chittagong threatened to paralyze cargo
handling in the port unless their demand is accepted forthwith.
"We will be then left with no option than resort to hardlines and
work stoppage," said convener of the Port Users Forum Kamaluddin
Ahmed.
</P>
<P>
This is for the third time the Port Users Forum is threatening
to go for work abstention in support of its demand for the right
to use private equipment in the cargo handling in the port.
</P>
<P>
On both occasions, the forum at last moment called off its
abstention program on request from the government's highest
authority who reportedly pledged to look into the demand
sympathetically.
</P>
<P>
The issue on the use of private equipment began from March this
year when a shipping company brought some of its equipment inside
the port jetty for handling its cargo, which was resisted by the
port's workers.
</P>
<P>
The port users also observed boycott in March demanding use of
private equipment, which was already permitted by the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The last the forum served notice for work abstention was on May
11. However, the boycott program was called off after a meeting
with Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina on the night of May 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
