<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loan to China for Water Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today approved a
400 million U.S. dollar loan for a water transfer project in China.
</P>
<P>
The Wanjiazhai Water Transfer Project will provide the physical
works needed to transfer water from the Yellow River to the Fen
River in northern Shanxi Province through a system of tunnels,
aqueduct pipelines and reservoirs.
</P>
<P>
The money also aimed to back policy and institutional reform
for economic water pricing and water marketing in the Yellow River
delivery system.
</P>
<P>
Besides water transfer, the project is also designed to work on
water pollution control and industrial waste management. 
</P>
