<HEADLINE> Car Sales Increase in Polish Market This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Poland has seen a sharp increase in
car sales during the four months of this year, according to a
report from Polish auto market investigation center.
</P>
<P>
The report said Poland has purchased 174,000 units of cars
during this period, up 30 percent compared to the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Among the total number of cars purchased, about 113,000 units
were made in Poland, up 4.7 over last year. The remaining are
Fiat, Daewoo, and Opel brands, which increased 35 percent, 23
percent, and 8 percent respectively compared to the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimated that car sales will increase 15-20 percent
each year. It was reported that 44.1 percent of people have
planned to buy cars within three years.
</P>
<P>
The rise in car sales was mainly attributed to hikes in
resident's income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
