<DOCNO> XIE19970604.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pollution-related Diseases Become Major Killers In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Respiratory diseases and cancer
have become one of the major killers threatening the health of the
Chinese people, said a report released by the National
Environmental Protection Agency (NEPA).
</P>
<P>
Research shows that respiratory diseases and cancer are closely
connected to the quality of the environment.
</P>
<P>
The latest report on China's environmental situation said that
the rate of death from respiratory diseases ranked the first and
the fourth respectively among all the causes of death in the
country's rural and urban areas last year, 1.61 per 1,000 persons
and 0.92 per 1,000 persons.
</P>
<P>
The report, written by a number of ministries and commissions
including NEPA and the Ministry of Public Health, also
revealed that the rate of death from cancer in the urban and rural
areas was 1.31 per 1,000 persons and 1.05 per 1,000 persons,
respectively in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The 1996 death rate from cancer in rural areas is lower than
1995's 1.11 per 1,000 persons; the first time since 1991 that the
figure has declined.
</P>
<P>
The report said that 65 pollution accidents happened last year,
leading to the illness of more than 4,300 people and the death of
10 people.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 41.5 percent of the accidents were caused
by urban waste water and 33.8 percent by industrial pollution.
</P>
<P>
The 17-page report, divided into two parts, gives details about
the achievements that China scored in environmental protection
last year and the problems that still remain.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Kunmin, deputy director of the NEPA, said that the
release of the report is to give the public a clear idea of the
country's environmental situation, improving people's
environmental awareness, and to promote global cooperation and
exchange.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970604.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
