<HEADLINE> Thai PM Makes New Proposal to Settle Border Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh has proposed that Thailand and Myanmar agree on a
permanent border to prevent future disputes, according to Mongkol
Ampornphisit, supreme commander of the Thai armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Mongkol was quoted today by local press as saying that Chavalit
asked him to propose to Myanmar authorities to use the middle of
the Moei river to demarcate the border to avoid problems resulting
from changes in the river's course or different interpretations of
the Thai-anglo treaty.
</P>
<P>
Mongkol said he will soon discuss the proposal with Thai army
commander-in-chief Chettha Thanajaro and ask the premier to assign
Chettha to lead a Thai delegation to Yangon to settle the issue
once for all.
</P>
<P>
Mongkol said the dispute over Myanmar's dredging of the Moei
river, which forms the border between Thailand and Myanmar, must
be handled with the consent of both parties.
</P>
<P>
An islet has been created in the Moei river because of a change
in the river's course, forcing the river further into Myanmar's
land, and Myanmar moved in heavy equipment and workers to try to
dredge the river to restore the river to its original position.
</P>
</TEXT>
