<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Bell Telephone Sells Well in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Bell Telephone
Equipment Manufacturing Company, a Sino-Belgian joint venture,
intends to increase the use of components made in China.
</P>
<P>
By 1998 up to 86 percent of the parts the company uses to
produce telephone switches will be manufactured in China.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Shanghai Bell, the country's
largest manufacturer of automatic telephone switches, produced 5.4
million lines of telephone exchanges in 1996 and earned more than
8.2 billion yuan in output value, more than half of the Shanghai's
telecom sector. It now has a 30 percent share of China's market.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 70 percent of parts for the company's major product,
telephone exchange S-1240, are from 82 companies in China.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications industry is a leading sector in Shanghai and
expects to bring in 3.5 billion yuan of output value annually by
the turn of the century. 
</P>
