<HEADLINE> World Boys and Girls Volleyball Tournaments to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The world boys and girls volleyball
championships will be held in Iran and Thailand respectively later
this year, the International Volleyball Federation (FIVB)
announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The world boys championship, to be held in Tehran, Iran, will
be staged from August 14 to 22. The tournament will draw teams
from host Iran, South and North American representatives of
Brazil, Cuba, Dominica and Venezuela, Asian teams of Chinese
Taipei, South Korea and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Teams from Europe are Italy, Poland, France, Greece, the Czech
Republic and Slovakia. Tunisia and Egypt will represent Africa to
the tournament, the FIVB announced in a press release.
</P>
<P>
In the girls tournament, the participating teams are host
Thailand, Argentina, Brazil, Japan, South Korea, Russia, Poland,
Ukraine, Italy, Slovakia, the Czech Republic, the Netherlands,
Cuba, Dominica, Nigeria and Mauritius.
</P>
<P>
The girls tournament will be held from August 2 to 10 in
Chiangmai, Thailand. 
</P>
