<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- South China University of Science
and Technology in the capital of Guangdong province has joined
hands with the local government and businesses to promote
education and develop research.
</P>
<P>
The university started the "join-hands" projects in 1993 and
has set up a number of community colleges in the field of electric
power, communications, electronic information, and paper-making
and environmental engineering with financial aid from local
government departments and businesses.
</P>
<P>
