<HEADLINE> France Draws Brazil at Tournoi de France Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- World champions Brazil and 1998
World Cup hosts France played to a 1-1 draw in the opening match
of the four-team Tournoi de France in Lyon on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Real Madrid's Roberto Carlos put Brazil ahead in the 21st
minute with a spctacular free kick, just to the right of center
and about 35 meters out, which curled round France's four-man wall
and in off Fabien Barthez's left post with the surprised Monaco
goalkeeper rooted to the spot.
</P>
<P>
France equalised on the hour when Ibrahim Ba darted through on
the right and fed Lyon's Florian Maurice, whose low shot was
blocked by the diving Taffarel. But fellow striker Marc Keller of
German club Karlsruhe pounced on the loose ball to nudge it into
the net.
</P>
<P>
England and Italy, rivals in the same World Cup qualifying
group, meet in the second match of the June 3-11 tournament, a
dress rehearsal for next year's World Cup finals, in Nantes on
Wednesday. 
</P>
