<HEADLINE> Mexican President Calls for More Efforts for Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo today called on all Mexicans to redouble their efforts in
striving for a vigorous, long-lasting economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Present the 1997-2000 National Program for the Financing of
Development (PRONAFIDE), Zedillo said that the current generation
will be the first in the country's history to enjoy economic
growth combined with total democracy.
</P>
<P>
He was optimistic over an economic growth because the
Pronafide's goals are both prudent and ambitious.
</P>
<P>
One of the program targets is to create millions of jobs every
year and reduce the number of the jobless.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, he said, an economic growth requires an increase
in investment on a systematic basis until it accounts for at least
25 percent of the gross domestic product by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Economic growth cannot depend "imprudently" on external
savings, he said. It should be complemented by internal savings.
</P>
<P>
Pronafide envisages actions that will strengthen the exporting
sector, promote foreign direct investment, ensure economic and
financial stability, improve credit conditions and maintain free
access to capital markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
