<HEADLINE> Holl Calls for Broad-Based Afghan government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Norbert Holl, UN special envoy on
the Afghan issue has said that "the only solution to the Afghan
conflict is a broad-based government".
</P>
<P>
Holl made the remarks at a press conference held in the Afghan
capital of Kabul Tuesday, according to a report reaching here
today.
</P>
<P>
Both the Taliban and their rivals paid only lip service to this
principle, because they selfishly wanted to keep power for
themselves, Holl said.
</P>
<P>
"A broad-based government is a system of power-sharing," Holl
added.
</P>
<P>
"All Afghan parties claim they support my peace initiative, but
unfortunately I have the feeling they see a military solution more
important than negotiation," Holl said.
</P>
<P>
Holl, who is in Kabul for talks with the Taliban, said that no
one "political or ethnic group" in Afghanistan is strong enough to
impose its rule on the whole country.
</P>
<P>
Holl said that he will visit the southern Afghan city of
Kandahar, the Taliban headquarters Wednesday, to resurrect the
concept of power-sharing.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to hold similar discussions with the opposition
alliance.
</P>
<P>
the UN special envoy ruled out any possibility of an immediate
ceasefire in the current Afghan fighting, which has dramatically
escalated in the past two weeks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
