<HEADLINE> Self-employed Help Laid-offs in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Self-employed businesses in
Nanjing, capital of south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, have been giving assistance to local laid-offs in
re-employment programs.
</P>
<P>
One hundred private businessmen in the city have volunteered to
help laid-offs who wanted to do business in looking for sales
stands, locating sources of goods, providing suggestions, and
offering business tips.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,000 yuan of funds donated by the self-employed in the
Hepin Store have gone to ten local workers who had been idle
because of their factories losing money.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that more than 1,500 state-run enterprise
laid-offs have since become self-employed laborers.  
