attended by over 200 people, including NZ cabinet members,
parliamentarians and business people, the Vice-Premier briefed
them on the current economic situation and the prospect for
long-term development in China.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that "there is a solid foundation and
favorable conditions for the further consolidation of the mutually
beneficial cooperation between China and New Zealand."
</P>
<P>
He welcomed NZ business people to invest in China to help the
further development of trade and economic cooperation between the
two countries.  
