<HEADLINE> World Junior Volleyball Tournaments to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The world women's junior volleyball
tournament will be held in Poland while the world men's junior
event in Bahrain this year.
</P>
<P>
The International Volleyball Federation announced in a press
release that the women's event will be held from September 5 to 13
in Gdansk, Poland. A total of 16 teams will compete in the event
and the draw of lots will be held on June 25 in Poland.
</P>
<P>
These teams are host Poland, continental tournament champions
Mauritius, China, Italy, Cuba and Brazil, and winners of the
continental qualification tournaments Japan, South Korea,
Dominica, Russia, the Czech Republic, Germany, Ukraine,
Yugoslavia, Kenya and Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The men's tournament will be held in Manama, Bahrain, between
August 21 and 29. The participating teams are Italy, Russia,
Greece, Latvia, Yugoslavia and Poland from Europe, Nigeria and
Tunisia from Africa, Bahrain, China, Chinese Taipei, Iran from
Asia, Venezuela, Mexico, Puerto Rico and Brazil from South and
North America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
