<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunting Field to Open to Overseas Visitors in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Forestry has
approved an international hunting field in northwest China's
Qinghai province, which will open to international visitors in
September.
</P>
<P>
Zhen Jie, director of the provincial wildlife protection
office, says that the 3,700-sq.km. area, named "International
Hunting Field at Qinghai Yellow River Source", is located in Maduo
county, near the source of the Yellow River, at a height of 4,200
meters above the sea level.
</P>
<P>
Named "International Hunting Field at Qinghai Yellow River
Source," it has three hunting sites providing habitats to 29 types
of animals and 20 types of birds.
</P>
<P>
Zhen says for the time being hunters can hunt four kinds of
amianls, namely, blue sheep, red deer, the white-lipped deer, and
Tibetan antelope, and each is allowed to bag at most three of the
games each time.
</P>
<P>
The area is 500 kilometer from Xining, capital of Qinghai. It
is complete with accommodations, communications and medical care
facilities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
