<DOCNO> XIE19970604.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Banana Exports Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica's banana exports rose
by 11 percent in April, compared with the same month last year
after a sustained drop in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter, Costa Rica exported 21.4 million boxes of
bananas, 25.6 million less than in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the National Banana Corporation (CORBANA) is
to export 127 million boxes this year, but the target appears to
be difficult to reach, due to the reduction in the first three
months.
</P>
<P>
Last year, banana exports brought in 576 million U.S. dollars
for banana growers. CORBANA plans to export 765 million dollars
worth of bananas this year, but it also seems hard to fulfill the
goal.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rican banana growers have joined other Latin American
banana growers to try to keep the United Banana Exporting
Countries (UPEB) alive.
</P>
<P>
Last week the UPEB held a meeting in Panama where member
countries agreed to set up a system of statistics on bananas on
the internet, which will help banana growers with their
decision-making. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
