<DOCNO> XIE19970604.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "No Losers" in Black Sea Fleet Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 3 (Xinhua) -- There is no winner or loser between
Ukraine and Russia following the signing of the three agreements
on the Black Sea Fleet last week, Ukraine Prime Minister Pavel
Lazarenko said today.
</P>
<P>
Neither Moscow nor Kiev had made compromises in the these
agreements. They were fully in the interests of the two countries,
Lazarenko told a press conference,
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko and his Russian counterpart, Viktor Chernomyrdin,
wound up disputes on the fleet by signing the agreements on May
28, paving the way for a broad friendship and cooperation treaty
sealed by Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma and his Russian
counterpart Boris Yeltsin on May 31.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements, Russia will lease for 20 years three bays
of Sevastopol -- Sevastopolskaya, Yuzhnaya and Karantynnaya-- as
its naval base.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko hopes to use the leasing fees to repay its gas debts
to Russia. He said the leasing fees were roughly equivalent to the
gas debt which stands at about three billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
