<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIFA to Tell French to Stop Hellebuyck Leaving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- World soccer governing body FIFA is
to tell the French Football Federation (FFF) to stop teenage star
David Hellebuyck leaving his club Lyon for 1996 Spanish champions
Atletico Madrid.
</P>
<P>
FIFA have decided that 18-year-old Hellebuyck, a junior French
international striker, could not have his letter permitting him to
join Atletico because he was under contract to Lyons till June 30
-- no player can be transferred from France unless they receive a
letter from the FFF allowing them to.
</P>
<P>
Hellebuyck, who was due to earn 2,500 pounds (3,750 dollars) a
week with Atletico's junior team who are in the second division,
had signed an agreement with the Spanish club on March 31.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Michel Aulas, the Lyon president, said that under the
present ruling he would demand a transfer fee for his young star.
</P>
<P>
"If he has to leave then it will cost Atletico at least 800,000
pounds," Aulas said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
