<HEADLINE> China, US Jointly Produce Microelectronic Components </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Microelectronic components are
being produced in a large scale in a Sino-US joint venture in
southwest China's Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
The Xunda Electronic Component Co. Ltd. produces component,
one-quarter the size of a grain of rice, widely applied in
electronic appliances, office equipment, and computers.
</P>
<P>
A joint venture between American Pacific Aviation &AMP; Technology
Corporation and Guiyang Vehicle Factory under the Ministry of
Railways, it uses the world's latest technology and equipment
which are specially designed for the production of surface mount
microelectronics components.
</P>
<P>
Besides 14 production lines in Guiyang, capital of the Guizhou
Province, the American Pacific Aviation &AMP; Technology Corporation
has put into operation another two production lines respectively
in Shanghai and Chishui, Guizhou Province.  
</P>
