<HEADLINE> Shanghai Bookstore On-Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Xinhua Bookstore on east
Nanjing road in Shanghai, the largest in the metropolis,
has been connected to a local computer network, becoming the
first on-line bookstore in the city.
</P>
<P>
Customers now have access to the bookstore's information and
service through the "Shanghai Hotline", a public access computer
network in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The on-line bookstore provides 40,000 kinds of books, and the
book information can be searched through the network in five ways.
</P>
<P>
Other information on books can also be gained through the
network, and readers' advice and requirements can be received by
the bookstore instantly through E-Mail.
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 people have visited the bookstore through the
network since it went into operation two weeks ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
