<HEADLINE> Japanese Bank Handles Renminbi Transactions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Branch of the
Industrial Bank of Japan (IBJ) has received 20-odd applications
for loans in renminbi since China approved foreign banks handling
renminbi transactions two months ago.
</P>
<P>
As one of the two foreign banks approved by the People's Bank
of China, China's central bank, the Industrial Bank of Japan
started renminbi operations on March 27.
</P>
<P>
The bank is to provide loans in renminbi to three or four
Japanese-funded firms which have intimate trade relations with
Chinese firms this month, said Kiyoshige Akamatsu, president of
the IBJ Shanghai Branch.
</P>
<P>
Transactions in renminbi only account for one or two percent of
the branch's total transactions. But the president predicted such
ratio will rise to 10 percent in the near future. 
</P>
