<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Slightly Higher in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Jobless rate in Chile was 6
percent between February and April, an increase of 0.2 percent
compared with the previous three months, the National Institute of
Statistics (INE) said today.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment figure, although slightly higher than the
previous quarter, was 0.1 percent below that of the February-April
period last year, the INE said.
</P>
<P>
In the three months this year, the labor force expanded to
5,590,470 people, an increase of 1.7 percent over the same period
in 1996. Jobs were created mainly in the commercial and financial
services sectors.
</P>
<P>
The number of workers employed in the financial service sector
increased 8.3 percent compared with the same period last year. And
in the construction and manufacturing sectors, the growth was 4.9
percent and 3.0 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, in the agricultural, hunting and fishery sectors, a
drop of 4.1 percent was reported.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment was down in nine regions in the country but
increased from 6.3 to 6.9 percent in the metropolitan area.
</P>
<P>
Joblessness among teenagers reached 14.3 percent with a slight
increase over the previous quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
