<HEADLINE> Injury May Keep Johnson From Athletics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Michael Johnson may drop out of
the World Athletics Championships in August because of a pulled
left quadriceps suffered in his 150m showdown against Donovan
Bailey.
</P>
<P>
"Michael couldn't bend his leg (Monday) and could be out for
two weeks to a month," said Clyde Hart, Johnson's coach.
</P>
<P>
If Johnson, the reigning Olympic 200m and 400m champion, is out
for that long it would deny him a chance to compete next week at
the US athletics championships in Indianapolis, the US qualifying
meet for the world championships at Athens.
</P>
<P>
Johnson suffered the injury in Sunday's "world's fastest man"
race against Canada's Donovan Bailey in Toronto. Bailey won in
14.99 seconds as Johnson pulled up about halfway into the showdown
with an injury. 
