<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China will set up a common property
rights market along the Yangtze River valley, an official source
said.
</P>
<P>
According to Luo Yulin, chief of the state property
administration of northwestern Qinghai Province, sponsors of the
common market are the nine property rights trading centers or
exchanges in the provinces and municipalities along the Yangtze
River -- Shanghai, Sichuan, Jiangxi, Jiangsu, Anhui, Qinghai,
Chongqing, Hunan and Fujian, said Luo, who participated in the
meeting last month.
</P>
<P>
As China's market-economy reforms go deeper, trading of
property rights has become increasingly common. 
