<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves $550 Mln Loans for Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today approved
three loans totaling 550 million U.S. dollars to Romania in
support of the new government's economic reform program.
</P>
<P>
The three loans include 50 million dollars for social
protection adjustment program, 350 million dollars for
agricultural sector adjustment program and 150 million dollars for
a second roads project. The fundings are designed to provide the
government with financial resources to fight poverty and cushion
the social cost of reforms while pushing ahead with economic
stabilization measures, reforming the country's large agricultural
sector, and improving its highways.
</P>
<P>
Since Romania joined the World Bank in 1972, the Bank's
commitments total over 4.7 billion dollars for its 50 projects.
</P>
