The Turkish-Cypriot declared a breakaway state in 1983 but it
is recognized only by Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Through the mediation by U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan and
the international community, President Clerides and
Turkish-Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash have agreed to hold direct
talks in New York to find a solution to the Cyprus issue. 
