<HEADLINE> German National Arrested in Greece for Drug Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Greek police today seized 50
kilograms of heroin when they arrested a German national for drug
trafficking in Corfu island, northwestern Greece.
</P>
<P>
Acting on information received, the police and customs
officials ordered 34-year-old Yassen Hoster to take his car off a
ferry-boat for a search which led to the discovery of the heroin
packed in 50 one-kilo slabs.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Hoster had driven to Greece from Istanbul
via Bulgaria, at the time of his arrest, he was heading for Italy
and his final destination is believed to have been Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
