<HEADLINE> Britain to Send Naval Support Ship to Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The British Ministry of Defense
announced here this evening that Britain was sending a naval
support vessel to the war-stricken Sierra Leone as the west
African country is quickly sliding into anarchy.
</P>
<P>
A British Ministry of Defense spokesman was quoted by the BBC
television as saying that the British government was sending a
naval ship named Argus to the area as a "prudent, precautionary
measure".
</P>
<P>
"The Argus is sailing towards Sierra Leone where she will be on
standby," the spokesman said, adding the 28,000-ton ship carries
Sea King helicopters and is equipped with a casualty receiving
center.
</P>
<P>
The British Foreign Office announced early today that the
British High Commission in Freetown (capital city) has been closed
and all British nationals should leave Sierra Leone immediately.
</P>
</TEXT>
