<HEADLINE> U.S. Says to Continue Aid for Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- the United States will
continue to provide aid to the Palestinians as it is "good for
the United States," the State Department said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the U.S. plan for the aid at a regular
briefing, State Department spokesman Nicholas Burns said: "We
are going forward with American assistance to the Palestinians
because it is good for the United States, it's good for the
Palestinians and it's good for Israel."
</P>
<P>
"It supports the peace negotiations" between the Palestinians
and Israelis, he added.
</P>
<P>
Burns told reporters that if the United States "pull the rug
out from under this assistance program", "we would be sending
the Palestinian people a very negative signal." 
</P>
</TEXT>
